diff:1620336968:1620336968:=1,72d0%0a%3c (:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c [[!EndangeredLanguages]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !Irula Language%0a%3c %0a%3c :Author: shreya_r%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Summary:''' \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Discussion of the endangered Irula language in South India%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Irula is a Dravidian language from the Tamil-Kannada subgroup spoken by the Irula people in the Nilgiri mountains. The language is very similar to Old Tamil with some influence from Kannada, and uses the Tamil writing system. It has around 12,000 speakers, and although its EGIDS classification is not available, Ethnologue lists it as a mid-sized endangered language with classification somewhere in the range 6b to 9, meaning that children no longer normally use and learn the language.%0a%3c %0a%3c Due to the close similarities to Tamil, some people argue that Irula is just a dialect and not its own language, contributing to some stigma around its use. This is partially because it is considered a more crude and less prestigious dialect due to its influence from other South Indian languages. Thus, Irula people typically do not speak the language outside of their own communities. They still use the language when practicing cultural traditions such as the dance and music performed in rituals, but this is mostly upheld by elderly members of the tribe. Their practices and language have been changing over time due to influence from other groups. However, funding has been put into revitalization programs, though I was unable to find specific information about such programs.%0a%3c %0a%3c https://www.ethnologue.com/language/iru%0a%3c https://indiantribalheritage.org/?p=30724#gsc.tab=0%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: B:)%0a%3c (:Category: EndangeredLanguages:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
